# What NOT to upload to Cloud Build. This file is a security boundary, not a
# size optimisation: `gcloud run deploy --source .` uploads everything not
# listed here and bakes it into the container image. Credentials must never
# make that trip - the whole point of the deployment is that the server holds
# no Webex credentials at all.

# Credentials and tokens - NEVER upload.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.wxcc/
*.token
*tokens*.json

# Local tenant config: names real customers, and means nothing to the server
# (the caller's token decides the tenant).
.mcp.json
.claude/

# Repo/tooling noise the runtime does not need.
.git/
.gitignore
.github/
hooks/
scripts/
docs/
*.md
!requirements.txt
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
build/
